    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-24T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.9111/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-24T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 24, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. The Department desires to study the text of the proposed Anglo-Soviet-Iranian
                    treaty in its final form. Please state what, if any, changes have been made in
                    the draft submitted as an enclosure to your despatch no. 169 of December 22,
                        1941.<note n="52" xml:id="d303fn52">Not printed.</note> What is the present
                    status of the proposed changes referred to in your no. 11, January 15, 1
                    p.m.?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
